## üîß CLI Commands

```bash
kalibr-connect examples          # Copy example files to current dir
kalibr-connect serve my_app.py   # Run your app locally
kalibr-connect version           # Show version info
kalibr-connect --help            # Show all commands
```

---

## ‚ö° Key Features

- ‚úÖ **Multi-Model Support** - Works with GPT, Claude, Gemini, Copilot
- ‚úÖ **Automatic Schemas** - No manual schema writing
- ‚úÖ **File Uploads** - Handle document uploads
- ‚úÖ **Sessions** - Stateful conversations
- ‚úÖ **Streaming** - Real-time data streaming
- ‚úÖ **Workflows** - Multi-step processes
- ‚úÖ **Type Safe** - Full Python type hints
- ‚úÖ **Fast** - Async/await support

---

## üî• Why Kalibr?

**Without Kalibr:**
- Learn 4 different API specs
- Write 4 different schemas
- Maintain 4 codebases
- = Weeks of work

**With Kalibr:**
- Write Python functions once
- Kalibr generates all 4 schemas
- Single codebase
- = One day of work

---

## üí° Simple Example

```python
# my_app.py
from kalibr import Kalibr

app = Kalibr(title="Weather API")

@app.action("get_weather", "Get current weather")
def get_weather(city: str):
    # Your logic here
    return {"city": city, "temp": 72, "condition": "sunny"}
```

```bash
# Run it
kalibr-connect serve my_app.py

# Now ALL these work:
# ‚úÖ ChatGPT can call get_weather()
# ‚úÖ Claude can call get_weather()
# ‚úÖ Gemini can call get_weather()
# ‚úÖ Copilot can call get_weather()
```

